==English==

===Etymology===
From both Czech ''[[robota]]'' meaning "[[drudgery]]" or "[[servitude]]" and from Slovak ''[[robota]]'' meaning "[[labour]]".  First appeared in a translation of the 1921 science-fiction play [[W:R.U.R. (Rossum's Universal Robots)|R.U.R. (Rossum's Universal Robots)]] by Karel Čapek.

